Uptime Kuma integration
-----------------------
Add a public /api/health endpoint (no auth) that pings all installed MCP instances.
Returns 200 + JSON status for the overall gateway, 503 if any instance is down.
Per-instance: /api/health?id=portainer-prod → 200 or 503.

The problem with the simple HTTP approach: user has to manually add one Uptime Kuma monitor
per MCP instance, which doesn't scale.

Better approach to investigate:
- MCPetty auto-generates the Uptime Kuma monitor config (bulk import via Uptime Kuma's
  backup/import JSON format) so the user just imports one file and gets all monitors at once.
- Or: MCPetty calls the Uptime Kuma API directly to create/delete monitors when instances
  are installed/uninstalled. Uptime Kuma has an undocumented but stable REST API + socket.io API.
  Credential needed: Uptime Kuma URL + username/password or API key.
  This would make monitoring fully automatic — install a Portainer instance, monitor appears.
